summary: This document is a Senior Indenture between Trustmark Corporation and Wilmington Trust, National Association, outlining the terms for issuing senior debt securities. It includes a cross-reference table aligning sections of the Trust Indenture Act of 1939 with the Indenture, and details provisions for the issuance, exchange, redemption, and security of the securities, as well as the roles and responsibilities of the trustee and securityholders.
